1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 g6 5. Bc4 Nb6 6. Bb3 Bg7 7. Ng5 e6 8. Qf3 Qe7 9. Ne4 h6 10. Bf4 {This way of maintaining the status quo is not effective.} Nc6 $5 {An interesting and principled continuation. Black delays the exchange on e5 in order to attack d4, too.} (10... dxe5 11. dxe5 Nc6 {is entirely playable, though.} 12. Nbc3 (12. Nbd2 {is a bit passive.} Nd5 13. Ba4 Bd7 14. Bxc6 Bxc6 15. Bg3 O-O-O 16. O-O-O h5 17. h4 f5 18. exf6 Nxf6 19. Qe3 Nxe4 20. Nxe4 Qb4 21. Nc3 Bxc3 22. Qxc3 Qxc3 23. bxc3 Bxg2 $15 {½-½ Abrahamyan,T (2397)-Yoo,C (2449) Saint Louis Winter-A 2019 (9)}) (12. Nf6+ Bxf6 13. exf6 Qxf6 14. Bxc7 Qxf3 15. gxf3 Nd5 16. Bg3 Nd4 $11) 12... Bd7 13. O-O-O O-O-O $11) 11. exd6 {The critical continuation.} (11. Qg3 dxe5 12. dxe5 Nd5 $17) 11... Nxd4 $1 {Leading to lively play.} 12. dxe7 (12. Qg3 cxd6 13. Bxd6 Nf5 14. Bxe7 Nxg3 15. Bf6 Bxf6 16. Nxf6+ Ke7 17. hxg3 Kxf6 18. Nc3 Bd7 19. Rh4 Bc6 20. f3 g5 21. Rd4 Rad8 $15 {0-1 Hartvig,O (2201)-Bach,M (2339) North Sea Cup 21st 2006 (9)}) 12... Nxf3+ 13. gxf3 Bxb2 14. Nbc3 Bxa1 {Black has won an exchange and a pawn. The pawn on c7 is hanging but so is that one on e7. White seems to have some initiative, but his possibilities are restricted because the bishop on b3 is passive. In some lines, it will be exposed to ...c5-c4, too.} 15. Nb5 (15. Be5 f5 16. Bxh8 fxe4 17. Rg1 c5 18. Rxg6 c4 $15 {0-1 Pourramezanali,A (2528)-Firouzja,A (2618) IRI-ch Bushehr 2019 (9)}) 15... Kxe7 16. Nxc7 f5 $5 $146 {Clearing space for the king.} (16... e5 {is more adventurous, since it weakens e5 and leaves the king exposed.} 17. Bd2 (17. Bg3 Bf5 18. Nxa8 Rxa8 19. Kd2 Rd8+ 20. Ke2 {1-0 Jain,K (2162)-Ter Sahakyan,S (2637) Titled Tuesday intern op 01st Feb-A blitz 2022 (7)} Bd4 $17) (17. Be3 Rb8 18. Bc5+ Kd7 19. Nb5 f5 20. Ned6 a6 $15) 17... Bf5 (17... Rb8 18. Bb4+ Kd7 19. Nb5 Ra8) 18. Bb4+ Kd7 19. Nxa8 Rxa8 $11) 17. O-O Bg7 18. Bd6+ Kf7 19. Nc5 Rd8 20. Bg3 Nd5 21. Bxd5 (21. Nxa8 f4 22. Bxd5 Rxd5 $17 {Black retrieves one of the attacked pieces, while the knight on a8 is still in danger.}) 21... Rxd5 22. Nd3 (22. Nxd5 exd5 $17 {with an extra pawn for Black.}) 22... Ra5 23. Nxa8 e5 24. f4 e4 25. Ne5+ Bxe5 26. fxe5 Rxa2 27. Nc7 g5 $44 {Black has fantastic compensation for the knight.} *

