{[%evp 0,56,27,21,53,64,64,59,59,48,48,48,48,48,50,44,44,44,44,44,44,30,43,48,43,25,35,19,33,33,33,7,31,24,31,-20,-10,-21,-16,0,0,29,6,41,41,41,41,41,41,24,34,34,-15,-15,-16,-16,-16,0,-8]} 1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. f4 dxe5 6. fxe5 Nc6 7. Be3 Bf5 8. Nc3 e6 9. Nf3 Be7 10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O f6 12. exf6 Bxf6 13. Qd2 Qe7 14. Rad1 Rad8 15. Qc1 {Even though this is played in the vast majority of games, it is not the strongest. Black can reach approximate equality by force.} e5 $1 {This and the next move are familiar to us already. The absence of the moves h2-h3 and ...Bg6 does not change anything essentially.} 16. d5 (16. dxe5 Nxe5 {does not bother Black.} 17. c5 Ng4 (17... Nbc4 {is simpler, at least in over-the-board games.} 18. Nd5 Rxd5 19. Rxd5 Nxe3 20. Qxe3 Nxf3+ 21. Rxf3 Be4 22. Rxf6 Qxf6 23. Rd1 Bc6 $11) 18. Rxd8 Rxd8 19. cxb6 Nxe3 20. bxc7 Rc8 21. Re1 Qc5 22. Ne4 Qb6 (22... Qxc1 23. Nxf6+ gxf6 24. Rxc1 $18) 23. Nxf6+ gxf6 24. Kh1 Rxc7 25. Qd2 Rc2 26. Bc4+ Rxc4 27. Rxe3 Be4 28. Ne1 Qc6 29. h3 Kf7 30. b3 Rc5 31. Qd4 f5 32. Rg3 Rc1 33. Rg7+ Ke6 34. Qd2 Qc3 35. Qxc3 Rxc3 $11 {Â½-Â½ Daillet,E-Alingh Prins,J EU-ch GT320 corr ICCF corr 1990}) 16... Nd4 17. Nxd4 (17. Kh1 Nxe2 18. Nxe2 Bg4 19. h3 {Â½-Â½ Todorovic,K (1935)-Ilic,Z (2136) SRB-chT3 North CS Sabac 2014 (2)} e4 20. Nfg1 (20. Nfd4 Bxd4 21. hxg4 Bxe3 22. Qxe3 Nxc4 $17) (20. hxg4 exf3 21. Rxf3 Bxb2 22. Qxb2 Rxf3 23. gxf3 Qxe3 $15) 20... Bh5 21. g4 Bg6 22. Nf4 Be5 23. Ne6 Rxf1 24. Rxf1 Re8 25. b3 c6 26. Bc5 Qh4 $132) (17. Bxd4 exd4 18. Nxd4 {This may seem to favor White slightly with respect to the previous similar line since the bishop on f5 is hanging.} Bg5 19. Qa1 (19. Nxf5 $2 Qc5+ 20. Kh1 Bxc1 $19 {0-1 Ladron de Guevara Pinto,P (2424)-Del Rio de Angelis,S (2525) ESP-ch 83rd Linares 2018 (5)}) 19... Bd7 {Due to his strong dark-squared bishop, Black has full compensation for the pawn.} 20. Kh1 (20. Qb1 Rxf1+ 21. Bxf1 Bg4 22. Re1 Qc5 23. Ncb5 (23. Qe4 Bf6 24. Qxg4 Qxd4+ 25. Qxd4 Bxd4+ 26. Kh1 Bxc3 27. bxc3 Kf8 {[%cal Gb6a4]} 28. Rb1 Rb8 29. Kg1 Na4 30. Bd3 g6 $11) 23... Bd2 24. Re4 Bf5 25. Kh1 Bxe4 26. Qxe4 Nd7 27. Ne6 Qf2 28. Qf3 Qxf3 29. gxf3 Rc8 30. Nbxc7 a6 {[%cal Gd2b4]} 31. a3 Bc1 32. b4 Bxa3 33. c5 a5 (33... Bxb4 34. c6 bxc6 35. Bxa6 Rb8 36. dxc6 Nb6 $11) 34. c6 bxc6 35. dxc6 Ne5 36. b5 Bd6 37. Nd5 Nxc6 38. bxc6 Rxc6 $15) 20... Bf4 21. g3 Be5 22. Qb1 c5 23. Ne6 (23. dxc6 Bxd4 24. cxd7 Bxc3) (23. Nf3 Bxc3) (23. Ndb5 a6) 23... Bxe6 24. dxe6 Bxc3 25. Rxf8+ Rxf8 26. bxc3 Qxe6 $11 {Â½-Â½ Conil,P-Cattoni,M FRA AJEC/1177 corr France 1988}) 17... exd4 18. Bxd4 (18. Rxd4 Bxd4 19. Bxd4 Rde8 (19... c5 20. Qe3 Qxe3+ 21. Bxe3 $44 {Â½- (41) Â½ (41) Lanc,A-Schmidt,W Brno 1975}) 20. Qd2 (20. b3 Nd7 $15) 20... Na4 $15) 18... Bg5 19. Qa1 c5 {Nothing new so far, but things will change slightly if we refer to concrete moves.} (19... Na4 20. Bf3 Be3+ 21. Bxe3 Qxe3+ 22. Kh1 Nxc3 23. bxc3 b6 {Â½-Â½ Perunovic, M (2569)-Berkes, F (2666) SRB-chT Subotica 2019 (10.3)}) 20. Bf2 {Unlike in the previous line, there is no exchange sacrifice on f2. Black has other ideas, though.} Bc2 {Just preparing the sacrifice.} (20... Bf4 $5 $146 {[%cal Ge7d6,Gb6a4]} 21. Rde1 Qd6 22. g3 Bd2 23. Rd1 Bxc3 24. bxc3 Nd7 $44) 21. Rde1 Rxf2 $1 (21... Bd2 22. Bg4 $146 Bxe1 23. Rxe1 $16) 22. Rxf2 (22. Kxf2 Qe3#) 22... Be3 23. Ref1 (23. Bf3 Bxf2+ 24. Kxf2 Qh4+ 25. Kg1 Nxc4 $11) (23. Nd1 Bxd1 24. Qxd1 Bxf2+ 25. Kxf2 Nxc4 26. Bg4 Qf6+ 27. Kg1 Qxb2 $5 28. d6 Nxd6 29. Qd5+ Nf7 30. Qxc5 Qb6 31. Qxb6 axb6 32. Re7 Nd6 $11) (23. b3 Bxf2+ 24. Kxf2 Re8 25. Bf3 Qh4+ 26. Kf1 Bd3+ 27. Ne2 Qxh2 $13) 23... Rf8 24. Qe1 (24. g3 Qe5 25. Kg2 Bxf2 26. Rxf2 Rxf2+ 27. Kxf2 Qd4+ 28. Kg2 Be4+ 29. Nxe4 Qxe4+ $11) 24... Nxc4 $1 $146 (24... Bd3 25. b3 $16 {Â½-Â½ Breitenbach,J-Briao,P BRA-ch7 f corr Brazil 1992}) (24... Rf5 25. Bf3 Bd3 26. b3 (26. Nd1 Bxf2+ 27. Nxf2 Re5 28. Nxd3 Rxe1 29. Rxe1 Qg5 $13 {0-1 Dushin, A (2440)-Siewert, W (2457) EU-ch65 sf08 email ICCF email 2003}) 26... Bxf2+ (26... Bxf1 27. Kxf1 $16) (26... Re5 27. Be2 Bd4 28. Kh1 $14) 27. Kxf2 Re5 28. Ne2 Qg5 29. Kg1 Nd7 $14) 25. Bxc4 Bxf2+ 26. Qxf2 Rxf2 27. d6+ Qf7 28. Bxf7+ Rxf7 $11 *

