11 18. f4 Qa5 $15 {0-1 Minic, D-Fischer, R Interzonal-08 Palma de Mallorca 1970 (14)}) (12. f4 $6 Nxc5 13. dxc5 d4 $17 {Â½-Â½ Patterson, L-Wright, S CAN-ch43 corr Canada 1986}) (12. Nxd5 Nxc5 13. Bc4 {Â½-Â½ Student, M (1880)-Schwarzkopf, J (1687) Harburg-chE 7th Hamburg 2009 (5)} Ne4 $15) (12. O-O e5 (12... Nxc5 $5 $146 13. dxc5 d4 14. Nxd4 Nxd4 $11) 13. Bb5 {transposes above.}) 12... e5 (12... Nxc5 13. dxc5 d4 14. Nxd4 Nxd4 $11) 13. Bb1 {This seems to be the main idea behind Rc1.} (13. dxe5 Ndxe5 14. Bb1 d4 $1 15. Nxd4 Nxd4 16. Bxd4 Bg4 {Black has devastating initiative.} 17. f3 (17. Qd2 Qh4 18. O-O Nf3+ 19. gxf3 Bxf3 $19 {mating soon.}) 17... Nxf3+ 18. gxf3 Qh4+ 19. Bf2 Qh3 20. fxg4 Bxc3+ $19) 13... exd4 14. Nxd4 Bxd4 $1 $146 {This is causing White certain troubles.} 15. Bxd4 Re8+ 16. Kf1 (16. Be3 $2 d4 $19) (16. Ne2 Qg5 17. Kf1 Rxe2 18. Kxe2 Qxg2 $17) 16... Qh4 17. Nxd5 {Fighting hard to stay in the game.} (17. Nb5 Nde5 $17) 17... Nxd4 (17... Qxd4 18. Qxd4 Nxd4 19. Nc7 $13) 18. Rc4 b6 $1 19. Qxd4 (19. Rxd4 Ba6+ 20. Kg1 Qxd4 21. Qxd4 Re1#) 19... Qxd4 20. Rxd4 Ba6+ 21. Bd3 bxc5 $19 *

