{[%evp 0,36,19,19,62,62,62,42,37,27,27,38,58,58,72,72,60,41,36,1,0,2,2,-29,-29,-29,-30,-57,-62,-73,-69,-69,-73,-61,-45,-71,-58,-75,-81]} 1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. exd6 cxd6 6. Nc3 g6 7. Be3 Bg7 8. Rc1 {This is White's most consistent try to face Black with problems organizing his counterplay. He does not make any kingside commitments and deprives Black of the possibility of playing ...Bg4.} O-O 9. Be2 {Still delaying the knight's development.} ({The main continuation,} 9. b3 {bears similar ideas and is examined in Lines 49 to 52.}) 9... d5 (9... e5 {is a worthy alternative.}) (9... Nc6 $6 {is less recommendable.} 10. d5 Ne5 (10... Na5 11. b3 $18) 11. b3 $14 {defending the knight on c3 is the main idea behind Rc1.}) 10. c5 (10. b3 dxc4 11. bxc4 Nc6 12. Nf3 Bg4 13. d5 (13. c5 Nd5 14. Nxd5 Qxd5 $11) 13... Na5 $15 {0-1 Kazakov,M (2400)-Kantorik,M (2305) Tatry op Tatranska Lomnica 1998 (4)}) 10... Nc4 11. Bxc4 (11. Nf3 {is not very inspiring for White.} Nxe3 12. fxe3 Bh6 13. Qd2 Nc6 14. O-O Bg4 15. Bb5 (15. b4 Nxb4 16. Rb1 Nc6 17. Rxb7 Bxf3 18. Bxf3 e6 $11) 15... Bxf3 16. Rxf3 e5 $11 {0-1 Frohberg,M (2197)-Varga,Z (2439) GER CupT 1617 prel2 Hamburg 2017 (2.1)}) 11... dxc4 12. Nf3 (12. d5 {is premature, due to White's poor development.} Na6 13. Nge2 Qa5 14. Qa4 Qxa4 15. Nxa4 Nb4 16. Rxc4 Nxd5 $17 {0-1 Malada, V (2249)-Palkovi, J (2454) Rijeka IM-B 2001 (6)}) (12. Nge2 {is less natural than the main move.} b6 $5 $146 13. Qa4 (13. cxb6 axb6 14. O-O Nc6 $15) 13... bxc5 14. dxc5 (14. Qxc4 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Ba6 $11) 14... Be6 15. Nf4 Qd7 16. Qa3 Nc6 17. O-O Rab8 18. Rfd1 Qc8 19. Nxe6 Qxe6 $11) 12... Nc6 {Since White has wasted a tempo on Rc1, which may be not especially useful, Black has a comfortable version of the classical line.} 13. Qa4 (13. O-O Bg4 14. h3 Bxf3 15. Qxf3 Nxd4 16. Bxd4 Qxd4 17. Qxb7 Qxc5 18. Ne4 Qd4 $15 {0-1 Berzina,I (2211)-Daulyte Cornette,D (2405) EU-ch blitz (Women) Monte Carlo 2019 (2)}) (13. h3 Bf5 14. O-O) 13... Bg4 14. Rd1 (14. Nd2 {0-1 Walther,E-Larsen,B Zuerich 1961 (10)} Nxd4 15. Nxc4 Rc8 $17) 14... Bxf3 15. gxf3 Nxd4 16. Bxd4 Bxd4 17. Qxc4 e5 18. Ne4 Qh4 $15 *

