{[%evp 0,36,28,18,54,62,62,29,37,11,8,10,9,32,27,30,30,2,9,-2,5,20,82,68,22,30,59,60,49,55,55,46,78,64,58,26,40,27,48]} 1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. c4 Nb6 4. c5 Nd5 5. Nc3 e6 6. d4 d6 7. cxd6 cxd6 8. Nxd5 exd5 {This exchange avoids the weakness resulting after ...Nxc3, but helps Black to clear the h3-c8 diagonal for his bishop.} 9. Nf3 Nc6 10. Bd3 (10. Be2 {keeps the d-file clear for the queen but is a bit passive.} dxe5 11. dxe5 Bb4+ 12. Bd2 Qa5 13. Bxb4 (13. O-O Bxd2 14. Nxd2 O-O 15. Nb3 Qb6 16. Qxd5 Re8 {Â½-Â½ Dely, P-Andersson, U Maroczy Memorial Debrecen 1970 (8) It is interesting to see that such a cautious player as Andersson played the Alekhine Defence occasionally.} 17. Qb5 Rxe5 18. Qxb6 axb6 19. Bf3 Be6 20. Rfc1 g5 21. Bxc6 bxc6 22. Nd4 Rxa2 23. Rxa2 Bxa2 24. Nxc6 Re2 25. b4 Rb2 $11 {Â½-Â½ Potapov, P (2493)-Shytaj, L (2435) Wch Rapid Doha 2016 (8)})) 10... g6 $5 $146 {This is possible because the pawn on d5 would not be hanging after ...dxe5, dxe5, while the pawn on d4 might be vulnerable after exd6.} (10... Bg4 {also makes sense after the bishop's development to d3.} 11. O-O dxe5 12. dxe5 Be7 13. Bf4 O-O 14. h3 Bh5 15. Rc1 Qb6 $5 $146 16. g4 Bg6 17. Bxg6 hxg6 18. Qxd5 Rad8 19. Qb3 Qxb3 20. axb3 Rd3 21. Rc3 Rfd8 22. Re1 Bb4 23. Rxd3 Rxd3 24. Re3 Rd5 {[%cal Gg8f8,Gf8e7] Planning ...Kf8-e7, when White would find it hard to make any progress. His queenside pawns are a permanent source of worries.} 25. e6 f6 $44) 11. O-O (11. Bg5 {allows} Qa5+ 12. Bd2 Qb6 $11) 11... Bg7 12. Bg5 Qc7 13. Bf4 (13. Rc1 O-O 14. b4 $5 dxe5 15. Nxe5 (15. dxe5 Qb6 $132) (15. b5 e4 $11) 15... Qd6 16. Nxc6 bxc6 17. Qd2 a5 18. bxa5 Qa3 $11) (13. exd6 Qxd6 14. Re1+ Be6 $11) (13. h3 dxe5 14. dxe5 O-O 15. Rc1 Qb6 $11) 13... O-O 14. exd6 Qb6 {White has got a far advanced pawn, but after the inevitable ...Nxd4, it will be rather unclear which passed pawn is more relevant.} 15. Rc1 (15. Re1 Nxd4 16. Nxd4 Qxd4 17. Bg3 Be6 {[%cal Gf8d8,Gg7f8] Planning ...Rfd8 and ...Bf8. We can see that the black passed pawn is by far safer than White's.} 18. Rc1 Qxb2 $13) 15... Nxd4 16. Nxd4 Qxd4 17. Bg3 Be6 18. Rc7 Qxb2 $13 *

