{[%evp 0,32,35,22,33,33,24,22,22,22,22,15,15,8,8,-9,-9,-13,-13,-11,-11,-10,-10,-10,-14,-10,-10,-23,-22,-14,-31,-30,-20,-20,-20]} 1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. c4 Nb6 4. c5 Nd5 5. Bc4 e6 6. d4 b6 7. cxb6 axb6 8. Bxd5 {By creating a target on d5, White hopes to force his opponent to make some concessions.} exd5 9. Nc3 (9. Nf3 Ba6 10. Nc3 Bb4 $15) 9... Nc6 $5 $146 {In this position, this is a novelty, but later we will transpose to a game featuring a different move order in the early phase. Black does not wish to make concessions such as ...c7-c6 or the relatively passive ...Bb7.} 10. Nxd5 {Â½-Â½ Horvath,T (1489)-Petrov,N (1799) Karvina op 2013 (6) The critical test.} (10. Nf3 Ba6 11. Bg5 (11. Nxd5 d6 $44) 11... Be7 12. Bxe7 Nxe7 $11) (10. Be3 Ba6 11. Nge2 Bb4 12. a3 Bxe2 13. Qxe2 Bxc3+ 14. bxc3 O-O 15. O-O Qe7 16. c4 (16. f4 f5 17. c4 Qf7 18. cxd5 Qxd5 $15) 16... Qe6 17. Rfc1 Ra5 $11) (10. Nge2 d6 11. exd6 Bxd6 $15) 10... d6 {White is hanging and his light squares are weak, so should play carefully.} 11. Bg5 $5 (11. exd6 Qxd6 $15) (11. Nf3 dxe5 12. dxe5 Be6 13. Nc3 Qxd1+ 14. Kxd1 O-O-O+ 15. Bd2 Bg4 $17) 11... Qd7 (11... Qxg5 12. Nxc7+ Kd8 13. Nxa8 Qxg2 14. Qf3 $16) 12. Ne2 (12. Nf3 dxe5 13. dxe5 h6 14. Be3 (14. Bh4 {takes the bishop far from d2.} Nb4 15. Nxb4 Bxb4+ 16. Kf1 Qxd1+ 17. Rxd1 g5 18. Bg3 Rxa2 $17) 14... Ba6 $15 {[%cal Ge8c8] followed by ...0-0-0. The white k9ing is stuck in the centre.}) 12... dxe5 13. dxe5 Ba6 {White once again has problems on light squares, but still hopes to get something out of his central activity.} 14. Nef4 Nxe5 15. Qd4 Bd6 16. O-O-O Bc8 $1 {Once the king has gone to the queenside, Black needs the a-file for his rook. The bishop could return into play via f5, sometimes with decisive effects.} 17. Rhe1 (17. Qc3 {may be a bit safer.} O-O 18. Bf6 Qf5 19. Bxe5 Bxe5 20. Ne7+ Kh8 21. Nxf5 Bxc3 22. Ne7 Bf6 23. Nxc8 Rxa2 24. Nxb6 cxb6 25. Nd3 g6 $11 {/î€®}) 17... Qc6+ (17... f6 18. Nxf6+ $1 gxf6 19. Bxf6 Qc6+ 20. Kb1 Bf5+ 21. Nd3 Rf8 $13) 18. Nc3 (18. Kb1 Bf5+ 19. Nd3 f6 20. Nxf6+ Kf7 $1 21. Rxe5 Bxe5 22. Qxe5 Ra5 23. Ng4 Re8 24. Qf4 Kg8 $17) 18... f6 19. Nfd5 O-O 20. Nxb6 Bg4 21. Nxa8 Bxd1 22. Rxd1 fxg5 23. Nb6 Qxg2 $15 *

